{
  "stem": "11964.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You couldn't study law or any such thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I-- I finally was able to gain admittance to the faculty of chemistry.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father, who was a great Zionist and who traveled a number of times in the 1930s to Israel, had the dream that I would eventually go to the Weizmann Institute in Rehovot.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At that time, it wasn't named Weizmann.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think it was Fisk Institute or such thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, anyway, he-- he sort of-- in a ceremonious way, he put down my name.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he says, you go and study chemistry here.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then when we are ready to leave-- and indeed he was going to sell his business, and we were all going to move to Israel.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that he planned to do in 1940, '41.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So of course, when I went to the university in Krakow, I realized I couldn't sit on the right side.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had to stand-- to sit on the left side, because I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We couldn't wear-- we were not allowed to wear the insignia of the university.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were certain caps that you would wear showing that you are a university student.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We could not wear it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in certain auditoria, we had standing room only.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So this hit me immediately, and I knew that we were second-class citizens.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When-- to answer your question, when I knew the danger existed was in August of 1939, when we saw certain kind of signs, politically and militarily and otherwise.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that is when we decided that we better think how to prepare for it and worry about what may come.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
